{"questionId":"11094","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">This question is about antiviral drugs.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Oseltamivir, used for the treatment of severe flu, is inactive until converted in the liver to its active carboxylate form.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Draw a circle around the functional group that can be converted to the carboxylate by hydrolysis.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/562319698210ee67ce0376b54b54f8e0ea09cfda.png\" width=\"329\" height=\"226\"></span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><img src=\"__IMG__/829d62ea6e046b2cef232e6d1fb6319804879488.png\" width=\"292\" height=\"206\">&nbsp;<strong>[<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">✔</span>]</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;<span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Accept circles that include the alkyl side chain.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11094","referenceCode":"19M.3.sl.TZ1.17a(i)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Draw a circle around the functional group that can be converted to the carboxylate by hydrolysis.","paper":"3","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(i)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry","D.5 Anti-viral medications","Options","D: Medicinal chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}